  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@Maaark I am sorry I won't have time to code this widget, I think given your level of understanding of the library you could give a try at doing it.\n\nYou could start with a simple:\n\n``` js\nvar widget = {\n  init: function() {\n    // define the options you need\n  },\n  render: function() {\n    // empty the select and update the options accordingly\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThere's one thing though that will not be feasible I believe is that you will not be able to hide some options if they are not matching any record, because we do not compute that data in Algolia REST API.\n",
